{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"054f27f5-3102-4f07-a61f-75657ef5c06f","content":"With Microsoft.Testing.Platform the flags change names and platform-specific args go after `--`:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter \"Category=Integration\" -- \\\n  --report-trx \\\n  --collect-coverage \\\n  --coverage-output-format cobertura \\\n  --crashdump \\\n  --hangdump \\\n  --hangdump-timeout 5m\n```\n\n**What changed:**\n\n| VSTest flag | Microsoft.Testing.Platform flag |\n|---|---|\n| `--logger trx` | `--report-trx` |\n| `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` | `--collect-coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura` |\n| `--blame-crash` | `--crashdump` |\n| `--blame-hang` | `--hangdump` |\n| `--blame-hang-timeout 5m` | `--hangdump-timeout 5m` |\n\n> **Note:** `--filter` stays on the left side of `--` (handled by `dotnet test`). Each platform extension requires its NuGet package: `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport`, `Microsoft.CodeCoverage`, `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CrashDump`, and `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.HangDump`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"200087bd-29bd-47d4-bff7-cc8752f28258","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating their CI test command from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MSTest runner) on .NET 8. Let me provide the equivalent command.\n\nKey differences with Microsoft.Testing.Platform:\n- `--filter` becomes `--filter`(same) or `--treenode-filter`\n- `--logger trx` becomes `--report-trx`\n- `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` becomes `--collect-coverage` with Microsoft.CodeCoverage, or you use a different approach\n- `--blame-crash` becomes `--crashdump`\n\n\n- `--blame-hang` and `--blame-hang-timeout` map to `--hangdump` and `--hangdump-timeout`\n\nThe command invocation changes too—with .NET 8, you're typically running the test project directly or using `dotnet test` with platform-specific arguments passed after `--`, though the newer Microsoft.Testing.Platform integration works more seamlessly starting with .NET 9 SDK.\n\nWith Microsoft.Testing.Platform on .NET 8, the test app becomes a standalone executable that `dotnet test` can still invoke, but the argument syntax shifts. The filtering and logging options change—things like `--treenode-filter` for filtering and `--report-trx` for TRX output replace the older MSTest-specific flags.\n\nWhen using `dotnet test`, platform-specific arguments go after the `--` separator, and I can chain multiple options together like coverage collection, crash dumps, and hang dumps with their respective timeouts. Alternatively, I can run the compiled test executable directly with the same arguments, bypassing `dotnet test` entirely.","outputTokens":1093,"requestId":"67E9:247AEF:29E08D7:2E2DC16:69FD34A6"},"id":"517e3d36-e31f-48de-bfd8-1d0dde3cce4c","timestamp":"2026-05-08T00:56:28.187Z","parentId":"90e32fb4-9c96-4154-b7f4-ab9e54ec3321"}
